text:
Two contract employees of the Pogo Mine were attacked on Monday while collecting geological samples.
Fatal black bear attacks against humans are very rare, but they do happen.
There have been several fatal attacks by grizzly bears on contract geologists in the last few years, often in remote areas.
As a bear awareness expert, we recommend:
- Be informed about the bear species that may be present;
- Know how to properly select and set up camps, and know what to do if you encounter a bear;
- Carry appropriate bear-safety equipment and know how to use it;
- Be proficient in using appropriate communication devices and understand the limitations of the devices;
- Keep an up-to-date bear plan;
- Know how to prepare an injured victim for transport; and
- Take a bear awareness course, such as the one offered by Grizzly Bear Outfitters Inc.
